```json
{
  "application": "Slurm",
  "details": {
    "resource_manager": "Slurm",
    "partition": "sched_mit_hill",
    "nodes": 2,
    "tasks_per_node": 16,
    "memory_per_cpu": "3500M",
    "time_limit": "2:00:00",
    "job_name": "merge",
    "output_file": "job_%j.out",
    "error_file": "job_%j.err",
    "environment": "dedalus",
    "executable": "python3",
    "command": "merge.py freeconvection_nh64_nz64_Q1_bfreq22891_DNS"
  }
}
```

This script utilizes Slurm as a resource manager. It requests resources from the "sched_mit_hill" partition, specifying 2 nodes with 16 tasks per node. Each CPU is allocated 3500 MB of memory. The job is named "merge" and has a time limit of 2 hours. Output and error logs are stored in "job_%j.out" and "job_%j.err" respectively. The script activates the "dedalus" environment using conda and runs "python3 merge.py freeconvection_nh64_nz64_Q1_bfreq22891_DNS" as the main command.
